But, though Dionysius and others represent him as obdurate and unmoved, this meaning seems improbable, as how could his firmness of mind be seen except by his steadi- ness of eountenanee? besides, it is scarcely credible that on such au occasion he did not evince some symptoms of humanity and fatherly love. Eminere usually means “ to be conspicuous cr remarkable.'’ Walker, with great probability, imagines that Livy intended to convey a different idea of Brutus from what Dionysius did.
